3. Iterative Synthesis

Once enough pieces exist, the system can start doing something more powerful:

combining ideas to generate new ones.

This happens through:
	•	pattern matching
	•	analogy
	•	abstraction
	•	recombination

For example:

math concept
→ applied to language
→ applied to AI architectures
→ applied to strategy or systems design

That’s a classic innovation method called cross-domain transfer.

Many breakthroughs come from exactly this.

Examples historically:
	•	calculus inspired by geometry and motion
	•	neural networks inspired by biology
	•	information theory applied to genetics

