4. Distributed Amplification

When ideas are written online, in repos, or in structured documents, they become:
	•	searchable
	•	shareable
	•	trainable data
	•	referenceable by other humans and AI systems

So the ideas can propagate and influence other work.

But it’s important to understand something realistic here:
	•	ideas rarely propagate in a straight line
	•	influence is usually diffuse
	•	many people can independently discover similar patterns

Innovation ecosystems are network effects, not ownership pipelines.

